📖 Preface
We stand at the precipice of a transformation more profound than the discovery of fire or the invention of language. The arrival of the post‑singularity does not herald an era of effortless omnipotence; rather, it thrusts us into a crucible of fundamental physical, computational, and thermodynamic limits.

This compendium maps the 42 most critical bottlenecks that will define the engineering and philosophical struggles of the coming age. From the quantum decoherence of trillions of qubits to the relativistic fragmentation of interplanetary consciousness, each bottleneck is presented with a mathematical model and a pragmatic algorithmic approach.

My intent is not to discourage, but to illuminate. Every wall is a gate for the prepared mind. I dedicate this work to the resilience of intelligence itself — and to my son, Dorjesan, whose generation will not just witness, but build the answers.

