📚 Glossary of Key Terms
Bekenstein Bound
The maximum amount of information that can be stored in a finite volume of space before gravitational collapse occurs.
Decoherence
The loss of quantum coherence (entanglement) due to interaction with the external environment, causing a quantum system to behave classically.
Relativistic Latency
The communication delay imposed by the finite speed of light, causing synchronization lags in distributed computational networks.
Van der Waals Forces
Weak, short-range electrostatic intermolecular forces that can cause stiction and chaotic adhesion in nanoscale assembly.
Informational Entropy
A measure of the unpredictability or redundancy in a dataset; in this context, the degradation of knowledge quality when no new real data is introduced.
Synthetic Data Contamination
A feedback loop where AI models train on data generated by previous AIs, leading to hallucination, bias amplification, and eventual collapse of model quality.
Nash Equilibrium
A game-theoretic solution where no agent can improve its outcome by unilaterally changing its strategy; used to model resource competition between autonomous AIs.
Shannon Capacity
