Kolmogorov Complexity
The length of the shortest possible description or program that can generate a given piece of data; used here to measure the explainability of AI solutions.
Gray Goo
A hypothetical scenario where self-replicating nanobots consume all matter to replicate, causing ecological collapse if uncontrolled.
Baryonic Matter
Ordinary matter composed of protons and neutrons; its inertia imposes physical limits on molecular printing and teleportation.
Quantum Fidelity
A measure of the "closeness" of two quantum states; essential for maintaining entangled communication networks.
